Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4. Line a 15x20cm/6x8in baking tin with greaseproof paper.In a pan, gently melt the butter (or margarine), golden syrup, black treacle and sugar until combined.Mix the remaining dry ingredients together in a large bowl.Add the hot syrup mixture and stir to combine.  Add the milk to help loosen the mixture.Pour into the prepared tin and bake for 35-45 minutes, or until springy to the touch.